      <p>Whether you're buying, selling, refinancing, or simply want to know what your home is worth, Las Vegas Appraisal Co. delivers certified residential appraisals you can rely on. With over 40 years of experience in the Las Vegas Valley, we provide detailed, defensible reports backed by current market data — delivered on time, every time.</p>

      <p>We are Nevada State Certified and FHA-approved, meaning our reports are accepted by lenders, courts, and government agencies throughout Clark County.</p>

      <h2>What Is a Home Appraisal?</h2>
      <p>A home appraisal is an independent, professional assessment of a property's market value. A licensed appraiser inspects the home, analyzes recent comparable sales in the area, and produces a written report detailing the property's estimated value. Appraisals are required by most lenders before approving a mortgage, and they're also useful for private buyers and sellers who want an unbiased second opinion on value.</p>

      <h2>When Do You Need a Home Appraisal?</h2>
      <ul>
        <li>Before buying or selling a home, to confirm the asking price is fair</li>
        <li>Before refinancing, to determine your current equity position</li>
        <li>For estate planning or probate purposes</li>
        <li>For divorce proceedings requiring fair property division</li>
        <li>When appealing your property tax assessment</li>
        <li>For legal disputes involving property value</li>
        <li>When making a significant renovation investment</li>
      </ul>

      <h2>What to Expect From Our Process</h2>
      <p>Our appraisal process is straightforward and professional:</p>
      <ul>
        <li><strong>Schedule:</strong> Call or text us at (702) 894-9279, 7 days a week. We typically schedule within 1–3 business days.</li>
        <li><strong>Inspection:</strong> One of our certified appraisers visits your property to measure, photograph, and assess its condition and features.</li>
        <li><strong>Research:</strong> We analyze recent comparable sales, neighborhood trends, and market conditions in the Las Vegas area.</li>
        <li><strong>Report Delivery:</strong> You receive a complete, professional appraisal report — typically within 2–3 business days of the inspection.</li>
      </ul>

      <h2>Why Choose Las Vegas Appraisal Co.?</h2>
